article.headline: Loyola of Chicago 66, Wis.-Milwaukee 56
article.story: MILWAUKEE (AP) -- Blake Schilb scored 15 points and J.R. Blount 14 to lead Loyola to 66-56 a Horizon League victory over Wisconsin-Milwaukee Wednesday night. The Ramblers (18-9, 9-5) won their fifth straight game. Andy Polka, a freshman who starred at Oshkosh West High School, and Majak Kou both added 13 points for Loyola. The victory clinched the No. 3 seed in the Horizon League tournament for Loyola behind Wright State and Butler, which are battling it out for first place. The high seed gives Loyola a bye in first round games Feb. 27. The Panthers (8-19, 5-9) lost their third game in a row. Paige Paulsen scored 16 points for Milwaukee and Avery Smith 10. Milwaukee scored the first six points of the second half to cut Loyola's lead to four points at 33-29. The Panthers narrowed the margin to four two more times but never got closer than that as the Ramblers remained in control of the game. Schilb scored 10 points to power Loyola to a 33-23 halftime lead.
